# Do not push to main without explicit approval

- **Never** run `git commit`, `git push`, or open a PR to `main` unless the user explicitly asks (e.g. “push”, “commit”, “ship to main”).
- Local work is fine; leave it uncommitted or on a branch until they say to publish.

## Test suite stays off main unless requested

Do **not** commit or push these to `main` unless the user explicitly asks for tests on the repo:

- `tests/` (automated `node --test` suite)
- `package.json` / `npm test` scripts added only for tests
- `js/catime-app-data.js` or other refactors done mainly to support tests
- `scripts/bug-test-storage.mjs` and `tests/README.md`

You may run tests locally (`node --test tests/*.test.mjs`) while developing. Do not treat passing tests as permission to push.

# Bug test before commit and push

Before **any** `git commit` or `git push` (only when the user explicitly asked you to publish):

1. Run `node --test tests/*.test.mjs` if `tests/` exists in the project (includes `mobile-layout.test.mjs` static guards)
2. **Mobile check (required when UI/CSS/HTML changed):** verify pages **work** and **look good** on a narrow viewport — not only that tests pass
3. Sanity-check other areas touched by the diff (auth, sync/import, watch player, comments behavior)
4. Fix failing tests and obvious regressions **before** staging or committing

Do not commit or push with failing tests or known-broken behavior in files you modified.

## Mobile bug test (work + look)

When `index.html`, layout CSS, watch page, comments, nav, or modals changed:

**Automated (required):** `mobile-layout.test.mjs` must pass as part of the full suite.

**Manual (required before commit/push):** Use browser DevTools device mode (or a real phone) at **375×667** and **390×844** minimum:

| Area | Works | Looks good |
|------|-------|------------|
| Home | Sections load; horizontal rows scroll | No overflow off-screen; hero readable |
| Nav | Hamburger opens/closes menu; pages switch | Logo and icons not clipped |
| Watch | Player loads; ep list scrolls; controls tap | Comments stack; Post full-width; actions grid neat |
| Search / List | Filters and rows usable | Text not microscopic; tables/cards fit width |
| Detail drawer | Opens/closes; actions tappable | Poster + text not overlapping awkwardly |
| Auth / Settings modals | Sign in/out; forms submit | Modal fits screen; inputs ≥44px tall |

If you cannot open a browser in the environment, say so and list what you verified statically; do **not** claim mobile was fully tested.

# Bump version before push

Before `git push`, update the release version so users and deploys reflect the latest build.

## User-facing version (required on every push)

In `index.html`, bump the footer label:

```html
<!-- footer -->
... v3.13</footer>
```

- Format: `vMAJOR.MINOR` (e.g. `v3.13` → `v3.14`)
- Increment the **minor** segment for each release push (project convention)
- Do **not** change `version: 3` inside `exportPayload()` — that is sync **schema** version, not the app release

## Service worker cache (when assets changed)

In `sw.js`, bump the cache name when `index.html`, `js/*`, or other cached assets changed:

```js
const CACHE = 'catime-v10';  // increment: catime-v11, catime-v12, ...
```

Bump `CACHE` whenever users must get fresh HTML/JS (same push as a footer bump is fine). Skip only if the push has zero client-file changes.

## Pre-push checklist

1. `node --test tests/*.test.mjs` passes (bug test — required)
2. If UI changed: mobile manual check done (works + looks good at narrow widths)
3. Footer in `index.html` shows the new `v3.x`
4. If client files changed: `sw.js` `CACHE` incremented
5. Version bump is included in the commit you are pushing (not left for a follow-up)
6. Commit message mentions the version when you ship features (e.g. `... and bump to v3.14`)

## Agent workflow

When the user asks to push (or you are about to run `git push`):

1. Run the full test suite; fix failures before committing
2. If UI/CSS changed: complete the mobile bug test table (works + looks good)
3. Check current footer version and whether `index.html` / `js/` / `sw.js` changed in the branch
4. Apply bumps if missing; stage those files with the rest of the push
5. Only then push

Never push release commits without updating the footer version.
